sections.heading: Definitions of inedible eggs3-703
sections.text: Definitions of inedible eggsIn this article, unless the context otherwise requires:1. "Addled" or "white rot" means putrid or rotten.2. "Adherent yolk" means the yolk has become fastened to the shell.3. "Adulterated eggs" are eggs that are filthy, putrid, decomposed
